    "symptom": "After each 60-second window rotation, the rate limiter stops enforcing limits entirely. All requests pass regardless of volume. count field is 0 after rotation. getDiagnostics().cache.size is always 0 after rotation, but getDiagnostics().store.entryCount is non-zero and growing correctly. The cache and store appear to be reading from different data sources. The bug starts immediately after the first rotateWindow() call and is permanent, not transient.",
    "rootCause": "hot-path-cache.js L40 captures the _counters object reference at module initialization time (constructor stores `this._map = counterMap` as a VALUE COPY). When counter-store.js::resetWindow() L36 reassigns `_counters` to a new Map, hot-path-cache.js::_cache._map still points to the old abandoned object. All cache reads go to the stale object (always empty after rotation), while all writes via incrementCount() go to the new _counters object. This is a permanent divergence — the cache and store are now permanently reading from and writing to different Maps.",
    "codeLocation": "hot-path-cache.js:40",
    "evidence": [
      "hot-path-cache.js L40: const _cache = new HotPathCache(_counters)",
      "counter-store.js L36: _counters reassigned in resetWindow()",
